**SUMMARY OF QUALIFICATIONS**

* Proven oral/written communications skills
* Ability to interpret design documents and review code 
* Four years of experience using JAVA
* Versed with SQL DML 

**SKILLS**

* Languages / Frameworks:

  * Familiarity with: C#, Python, AJAX/XHR, ReactJS, T-SQL, MySQL

    Technologies: VisualStudio2015, Eclipse, Git, dependency injection, repository pattern, Node.js, MongoDB, mLab, Robo 3T, SQL Server, Oracle SQL • Other Skills: agile and waterfall methodologies, SCRUM, unit testing, MS Office (Word, Excel, Outlook, Access)   EDUCATION Glendale Community College, Glendale, AZ – December 2019 Associate of Science (Computer Science) Associate of Science Associate of Arts Academic Certificate in Communication Competence in the Workplace 

 

Academic Achievements: President’s Honor List (Fall 2012 and Fall 2019) Student Recognition Award for Outstanding Contribution for Sigma Chi Eta Phi Theta Kappa, President Sigma Chi Eta, Secretary 

 

Woz-U, Scottsdale, AZ        04/2018 – 06/2018 Front-end frameworks with ReactJS. Acquired skills to program using JavaScript, and build databasedriven web applications using MongoDB, JavaScript, and the ReactJS library.    

 

EXPERIENCE Tutor, Math Solutions, Glendale Community College, Glendale, AZ  01/2013 – 12/2015 • Assist students with math problems ranging from MAT082 to MAT267 (remedial algebra through differential equations) • Worked one-on-one with students in MAT108 course to find solution to achieve academic success in their math courses 

 

Tutor, Computer Science Solutions, Glendale Community College, AZ  01/2013 – 12/2015 • Assist students with general programming related issues, including languages such as C, C++, Java, Prolog, and LISP 

 

Supplemental Instructor, Computer Science, Glendale Community College, AZ Spring 2014 • Attend computer science classes taught by supervising professor, host directed tutoring sessions for approximately 18 students • Work one-one with students on object-oriented programming concepts in JAVA, computer systems, and fundamental algorithm techniques
